Two type of Rest API
1. HTTP Request
2. SOAP/XML-RPC Request


Test Plan
 |---Thread Group (Users)
	|---Sampler (Request): HTTP Request
	|---Listener(View Result): View Results Tree



HTTP Request
=========================================
Name: HTTP Request
Server Name or IP: api.openweathermap.org
Protocol[http]:       // if it is "https" then type here 
Path: /data/2.5/weather

Paramerters
====================
Name		Value
-----------------------------------------------------------------
q	| 	Dhaka
-----------------------------------------------------------------
appid	|	5ad76b332e2fa27ea9859353e5fdd69d


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Test Plan
 |---Thread Group (Users)
	|---Sampler (Request): SOAP/XML-RPC Request
	|---Listener(View Result): View Results Tree

SOAP/XML-RPC Request
=========================================
- SOAP/XML-RPC Request setting is more easy than HTTP Request
- We can set full server url , path and parameter in "Server Name or IP"

Test Plan
 |---Thread Group (Users)
	|---Sampler (Request): SOAP/XML-RPC Request
	|---Listener(View Result): View Results Tree



SOAP/XML-RPC Request
====================
Name: SOAP/XML-RPC Requestt
Server Name or IP: api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=Dhaka&appid=5ad76b332e2fa27ea9859353e5fdd69d

